      "writtenOn": "2026-05-06T12:06:08Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Thanks for the suggestion. After re-reading the document in the following link:\n`https://github.com/openbmc/docs/blob/master/architecture/sensor-architecture.md`\n\nI would prefer to keep the parameter as `const std::optional\u003cstd::string\u003e\u0026 inventoryPath` rather than `std::vector\u003cstd::string\u003e\u0026 associatedPaths` for 2 reasons:\n\n1. The function only ever emits the two association pairs documented for sensors - `chassis`/`all_sensors` and `inventory`/`sensors` - and the chassis path is derived internally from `configurationPath`. So the only thing the caller actually supplies is an inventory item path. Renaming to `associationPaths` would suggest the caller can pass non-inventory paths, which the function does not support.\n\n2. For the GPU sensors in this patch, each sensor monitors exactly one hardware item (its parent GPU), so a single `std::optional` cleanly expresses \"this sensor has one inventory parent, or none.\" I would prefer to keep the API matched to the actual usage rather than pre-generalize.\n\nIf a future use case emerges where one sensor genuinely needs to associate with multiple inventory items. I\u0027m happy to change the signature to `std::vector` then. Does that work for you?",
